next
  Summary: Loot Balance. Online NPCs are continuously trimmed so long-lived stalkers (story NPCs, companions, gulag survivors) never accumulate corpse-sized hoards. Traders are skipped so their stock is untouched. Smart Pacing renamed to Smart Balance (label only, no behavior change).
  Added:
    Added: Loot Balance. Periodic scanner walks online stalkers in small batches and trims each one at most once per game-day. The population that survives is the population that hoards, so hundreds of long-lived stalkers kept driving save bloat, server-object inflation, and steady performance drag under the previous death-time approach. The scanner closes that gap. Per-category cull ceilings from xinventory categories (medkit, bandage, antirad, stim, pill, food, drink, ammo_not_equipped, weapon, outfit, helmet, artefact, device, crafting); anything above the ceiling is released. Quest items, equipped gear, and untouchables (xinventory pre-filters quest / anim / blacklisted) are never touched. Traders are skipped at the scheduler level (xcreature.is_unscriptable). Public API at module scope (trim_npc, evaluate_item, build_state, default_policy) lets probes, MCM buttons, and other mods drive trimming externally or compose with the default policy. MCM (General -> Loot Balance) defaults: enable on, NPCs per frame 1, NPCs per cycle 20, per-NPC rescan cooldown 24 game-hours. Requires NPC corpse looting enabled. Disable "311- NPC Stop Looting Dead Bodies - DTTheGunslinger" or any equivalent NPC-loot disabler for full benefit.
  Changed:
    Renamed: Smart Pacing is now labelled Smart Balance in MCM, readme, and architecture. Label only, no behavior change. Internal script and config keys (ab_pacing, last_respawn_update, advances, min_minutes) unchanged.
    Changed: Smart Balance death counter credits every non-vermin death. Previously dropped story-NPC, trader, named-NPC, task-giver, companion, and task-target deaths via xsquad.is_protected.
    Changed: Loot Balance scanner enable-tooltip rewritten to describe the current per-category cull ceiling algorithm. Old text referenced the dropped [keep_one] / [keep_items] / surplus_per_category scheme that pre-dated the xinventory category restructure.
  Removed:
    Removed: orphan MCM strings ui_mcm_ab_general_surplus_per_category and _desc (eng + rus). The MCM key was dropped from defaults earlier; the string table entries lingered as dead text.

1.0.2
  Summary: Crash fix on xlibs 1.7.0
  Fixed:
    Fixed: Crash in Smart Pacing on xlibs 1.7.0 at ab_recipe.script:141. Adopt renamed xsmart.find_smarts_spawning (was xsmart.find_smarts_with_recipe pre-1.7.0). Requires xlibs 1.7.0+.

1.0.1
  Summary: Crash fix on malformed respawn params, third-party respawn-delay compatibility
  Fixed:
    Fixed: Crash in Smart Pacing budget evaluation when scanning malformed or misconfigured smart terrains whose respawn_params.num condlist has no default branch.
  Compatibility:
    Skip smart terrains whose last_respawn_update is set to a future game-time by another mod. Honors third-party deferred-respawn intent instead of overriding it.

1.0.0
  First release. Advances respawn cooldowns at smart terrains where combat has produced deaths, so active regions recover faster without affecting the rest of the map.
